9:
Why, yes! That AND a
meet-and-greet between the
merchants and those from
Hakunroh who stayed behind.
14:
In other words, you'll be using a
banquet as a means to forge
relationships between all the
attendees.
18:
Those connections can be very
important. Thanks to Lilie, I've
dabbled in everything from sales to
clerical work.
20:
Now making money's nice, but what
these girls need is to interact with
others and find a place they can
call their own.
25: Heh-heh. You don't miss a thing!
28:
Oh, but partying is still the main
draw! We received so many
donations, it's only right we show our
patrons some appreciation.
30:
As thanks for all of your help, you
can just leave all the planning to me.
33:
Oh, and Alk, I sincerely hope you'll all
be joining us!
38:
I dunno... We'd probably just get in
the way.
43:
Not in the slightest! It would make
me more than happy to see you
darlings having a good time too.
47: Then... Sure, we'd love to go!
57:
Just please don't get carried away.
The festival will be winding down.
Best to keep things simple and
tastefulâ€”
64:
This is exactly what I was worried
about!
68:
I should've known this is what she
had in mind...
72:
Madam Eva helped out a lot with the
establishment and staffing.
76:
I think it fits the sensibilities of our
patrons like the silkiest glove you'd
ever find!
80:
M-maybe, but don't you think this
place is a bit... questionable?
84:
Now, now. It's not polite to pass
judgment like that.
88:
Besides, Madam Eva has made it
explicitly clear what's to be allowed
and what isn't, so everyone can
enjoy themselves!
93:
Don't get your tail in a twist about it!
The only thing questionable is
what's runnin' through your mind, I'll
bet.
97:
I have a nice, quiet table ready for
everyone. Please, just follow me!
104:
Mr. Takamori! I'm so happy to see
you here!
121:
Heh, now there's a face I didn't
expect to see.
127: Th-this... isn't what it looks like!
132:
Not that this s-sort of place isn't
respectable, but still... it's not what it
looks like!
137:
Tee-hee. Calm down, you silly boys.
I'm the one that invited Mr. Takamori
here.
141: I think of us as companions of a sort.
146:
She came to me asking if I'd like to
check things out and maybe make
some connections.
151:
There are some people who simply
thrive at night, no matter how much
you try to coax them into a different
lifestyle.
156:
And, at the moment, there's no
outlet for that in Shibuya. We can't
just let those types run loose, though.
161:
You both need to rely on Palpebra.
Now I see what she means by
"companions."
166:
Well... It's good to make progress,
right?
170:
Yes, but honestly, I'm not very
comfortable in places like this...
175:
Don't you worry about a thing! I
promise to show you a WONDERFUL
time.
178:
Making connections for the girls...
Helping out with the situation in
Shibuya... What about your own
personal goals, Kikuno?
182:
Tee-hee! I've already got things in
motion!
185: Sorry to intrude on all the festivities!
193:
Kikuno, here is the deed for the sign
you asked about. There were no
problems getting it.
197:
Hehe! It was even easier than I
expected. A little sob story goes a
long way!
202:
Oh... Is this about Hakunroh? I
thought the Academy was
overseeing it...
207:
That's why I put in a special request.
"If nothing else, please let me have
the sign. *sniffle* Pleeeease!"
210:
Tee-hee! So, here's the plan! Yours
truly is going to open up the second
run of Hakunroh!
213:
And the staff won't just be from
Palpebra. We're looking for
employees from Shibuya, too!
217:
I'm making a roost for ALL of those
poor little chicks who don't have a
place to go!
226:
But of course! Even before you set
down roots, you must know how
high you're looking to grow!
229:
The only issue is... I haven't NEARLY
the amount of money I need. This
dream is still years away, if not
decades. But who knows?
235:
If it's all right w-with you... I'd love to
work at the new Hakunroh with you,
Kikuno!
238:
Really?! Y-you did just hear that this
dream of mine is still far down the
road, right?
241:
I haven't even planned out the type
of establishment it'll be or anything
else important. There are so many
decisions to make!
244: I know! Still... I'm on board!
246:
How much would it cost to get
things going?
248:
Hey, you're not gonna get a jump on
things this time! K-Kikuno, you can
count on my investment, too!
257:
I humbly accept all of your
kindness...
262:
You can place your faith in me! I'll
shoulder the burden with a beaming
smile!
265:
...
Thank you all. I was right...
268:
*sniffle* I am truly blessed to have
such friends...
